The paper deals with the problem of testing linearity of a function in a distribution-free setting, which is a fundamental problem in property testing. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also uses techniques from information theory and machine learning, which makes it relevant to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with testing functions on R^n, which is a topic in computational geometry and computational topology, making it relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Computational Geometry).
